ve been thinking a lot about advertising the guild, what direction we want to go, and how fast to grow. Here are a few of my thoughts.<br>
<br>
This weekend’s newbie events in Neriak will be a test run. While getting some experience running the games we may pick up a few prospects while seeing what games the newbies like best and what prizes are most appreciated.<br>
<br>
August 5, 2000 – Have the web site converted to frames. Put up a member’s page that list all members along with their race and class and links to their RP story. Fully integrate Lexxii’s application page, and start using a formalized process for accepting new members into the guild. Post the story of Midnight Council.<br>
<br>
August 12 – Have an information section on the web site dedicated to helping newbies of evil race or class. Tips on how to succeed in the game as an evil character, and links to many of the good player and skill guides. 30 registered members that enjoy playing evil in a nice way and will take the time to help newbies.<br>
<br>
August 19 – Plan a big “Day of Evil Celebrations” event which will span all evil cities, plus have representatives at Ak’anan, Grobb, Ogguk, Qeynos, Freeport, and Erudin. Contact other guilds or players that may want to take part. Have the web site ready for a major publishing push. Send information to eqvault and the other major EQ sites letting them know about our plans for “Day of Evil Celebrations”.<br>
<br>
August 26 – The big “Day of Evil Celebrations” is here. We have a few contests at each city that has representatives in our ranks. Assist character that would like to relocate to Neriak, have a few games, and sponsor a big drunken bash at newbie log on Saturday night. We can even to a small fireworks display by creating magicians with the flair spell to stand on the big hill behind newbie log and fire the flares out over Nektulos Forest. Hopefully reach a goal of 40 good members. Have a disciplinary council in place with finalized rules and procedures stated on the web site. Start organizing event in other cities and spread our name in the playing community.<br>
<br>
So, what are your thoughs? <p><P><B><FONT COLOR="#FF0000">Reog</FONT></B> the educated ogre of <A HREF="http://www.midnight_council.homestead.com"><IMG SRC = "http://www.midnight_council.homestead.com/files/mcsmall.gif" WIDTH=195 HEIGHT=32  BORDER=0></A></P>
<P><B><FONT COLOR="#FF0000">Arlo</FONT></B>/<B><FONT COLOR="#FF0000">Tinkerdo</FONT></B>
      - You spawn it, we kill it.</P>
    
    <P><B><FONT COLOR="#FF0000">Rabid</FONT></B> - lost druid from Tunare.</P></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#242422><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub20.ezboard.com/usyzian.showPublicProfile?language=EN>syzian</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>   <font color=#939393>(7/28/00 8:32:18 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The four-week plan.</span><hr size=1> It sounds good!  We will have to work hard to make this really go well!  That would be awesome though!  I'm excited!  Our server is great but it needs more stuff for newbies.  More events and just plain fun.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><A HREF="MAILTO:thespek@hotmail.com"><B>Syzian</A></B><BR>
