</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub20.ezboard.com/umalekithe.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Malekithe</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_magentaspot.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>   <font color=#939393>(7/28/00 11:28:21 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The four-week plan.</span><hr size=1>   I am of the impression that we may be getting ahead of ourselves. First thing we should do, is organize the people we have now. Then, at a later date when we have all our I's dotted and T's crossed, we can open the flood gates to the hordes that want iN.<br>
<br>
  You have to learn to walk, before you can run.<br>
<br>
  I would love nothing more than to be able to hit the ground running, but we have to be realistic. Most of us (if not all) are new at this whole guild thing, let's not bite off more than we can chew.<br>
<br>
  I will try to help out with anything that needs assistance, as much as possible. I unfortunately cannot make promises, as my wife and daughter &quot;got dibbs&quot; on my time. Aside from them, the rest of my free time, I am ready and willing to get my hands dirty, my feet wet, and my sword bloody.<br>
<br>
  On the members page that will be in production in the near future... are we going to include rudimentary RL info? <br>
<br>
I'm talking things like: <br>
  first name<br>
  gender<br>
  age<br>
  city<br>
  state<br>
  occupation<br>
  a pic (if we dare show our faces to the public).<br>
<br>
  Nothing too &quot;pin-pointing&quot; (after all, does Lexxii want THAT many stalkers? I HOPE not!) but a basic portrayal of the folks we call brother and sister.<br>
<br>
  Anyway... just some ideas I had flying around between my ears. <p><br>Malekithe
<br>Dark Elf Shadow Kight</p><i>Edited by <A HREF=http://pub20.ezboard.com/umalekithe.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Malekithe</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_magentaspot.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10> at: 7/28/00 12:03:28 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#242422><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub20.ezboard.com/uobeah.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Obeah</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>   <font color=#939393>(7/28/00 11:37:53 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The four-week plan.</span><hr size=1> I don't think we are getting ahead of ourselves. Reog has planned things nicely. This event saturday will serve as a test model for future events. We need to set an agenda for our guild. I have been in guilds where the only thing we did was meet once a month. Other than that it was bright green /ooc.<br>
<br>
The timeline for the website is fine.<br>
<br>
The timeline for the Evil Festival is also good and gives plenty of time for flexibility.<br>
<br>
We just have to make sure WE take the necessary steps to adhere to this and work to achieve our goals. <p><p align="left"><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="+2" color="#FF0000"><b><font size="+1">Obeah<br><a href="http://www.midnight_council.homestead.com"><img src="http://fantazone.com/mcresources/mcsig.jpg" border=0></p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub20.ezboard.com/bmidnightcouncil.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=saskia>Saskia</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>   <font color=#939393>(7/28/00 1:49:55 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The four-week plan.</span><hr size=1> I think it sounds excellent<br>
<br>
I run my own guild on Rallos Zek, but in all honesty wasnt sure how to start off some events for my guild..with Rallos being a pvp theres always the rsik of it being raided by PK Guilds (its happened at weddings etc) so I've put it on the shelf, so this will be a great learning experience for me =)<br>
<br>
I really like the idea of a RL intro to our chars aswell, I'm in a guild on another server and there are real life pics of us all on there, and it went down really well, true friends come out of this game (ive met some rl) and its so nice to see who you partner with all the time, or who you laugh with in /gu...I myself would really like to see that happen =)<br>
<br>
Oh, and I dont mean to be fussy, as I think I'm the only brit in the guild, but I really would like to be involved in this so I'm hoping it wont be tooooo late, im 8 hours ahead of PST, 6 ahead of CST and 5 ahead of EST..dont worry if you have to make it late tho, if i get enough caffiene in me i can prolly do an all nighter hehe<br>
<br>
So all in all a big thumbs up from me..I cant wait!<br>
